      <description lang="en">The COLLECT speech database, supplied by CSELT, was recorded in Italy, in 1987 by 500 speakers; half of them called using Turin phones and the other half from all over the country. They were automatically prompted to utter 15 words (the 10 Italian digits and 5 command words - Yes, No, I accept, I refuse, Yes I accept). Each word was collected by digitally recording the utterances.</description>
